                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Providence</placeName>\n                <date>July 28<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1856</date>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(11)\">\n                <placeName>Phila</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear &amp; rev. Sir!</p>\n            <p>I take the liberty to <sic>adress</sic> a<lb/> few lines to you again but<lb/> first\n                of all let me thank you<lb/> for your kind letter and valuable<lb/> advice which you\n                    <sic>was</sic> kind enough<lb/> to address to me. The object<lb/> of this here\n                my letter is for<lb/> a different one, but at the same<lb/> time very important.</p>\n            <p>In our city here lives a man<lb/> who is a „<hi rend=\"underline\">Meshumcth</hi>”<lb/>\n                He is in Thorah and Talmud<lb/> very well versed, having been a<lb/> teacher in\n                    <placeName>Kracow</placeName>, but when<lb/> about 17_18 years old he was<lb/>\n                persuaded by an English Missionary<lb/> to commit that fatal crime to<lb/> desert\n                his religion. But now<lb/> he is really repentant of it and<lb/> wants to become\n                again<lb/> a „member of <placeName>Israel</placeName>.”</p>\n            "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3qb9vr9x/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
