                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3qb9vr9x/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p>The man is a cigar maker here<lb/> and makes a living but has not<lb/> funds enough\n                to go to <placeName>N. York</placeName> for<lb/> some time to accomplish his\n                object<lb/> neither has he friends or acquaintances<lb/> there to help him, but now\n                my<lb/> dear isr, what shall we do to<lb/> assist him and in fact what is<lb/>\n                necessary for us to do in regard<lb/> to him. We are all <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >young</hi> and<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">inexperienced</hi> mautheraud<add>?</add> truly<lb/> need the\n                guidance and <sic>advises</sic><lb/> of such a man as you sometimes.<lb/> We do not\n                know much about<lb/> our religion, all we know is we<lb/> were born Jehudim and want\n                to<lb/> die as such, following the <hi rend=\"underline\">old</hi> Belief<lb/> of our\n                fathers <del>wh</del> without making<lb/> additional safety wolves on, to the<lb/>\n                old Religion, in order to suit<lb/> our convenience better, than our God,<lb/> as\n                some of the Reformers do.<lb/> But guidance we need once and<lb/> a while, &amp;\n                then I shall always take</p>\n            "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3qb9vr9x/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
